Key Match Events: Jose Altuve and Jeremy Peña homered, with Peña's three-run shot capping a five-run sixth inning.
Kevin Newman homered off Kikuchi in the fourth.
Yordan Alvarez’s two-out RBI single put the Astros on top.
Alex Bregman capped the flurry with a bases-loaded walk.
Pre-Game Insights: Houston improved to 7-0 in games started by Yusei Kikuchi.
Arizona, which has dropped three straight and seven of 10, holds a half-game edge over the New York Mets for the second National League wild card.
Post-Match Reflections: Diamondbacks manager Torey Lovullo mentioned mistakes defensively and in execution.
Astros manager Joe Espada praised the team's offensive approach saying Peña's opposite field homer was a key swing.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Eugenio Suárez hit his 25th homer in the sixth to bring Arizona within a run.
Dylan Floro was charged with all five Houston runs in the sixth.
Rodriguez gave up five runs, four earned, and seven hits over four innings.
Others: Diamondbacks: C José Herrera returned to the lineup after being hit on the back of the helmet.
Astros: Kyle Tucker was available off the bench after a 79-game absence due to a fractured right shin.
Mauricio Dubón is dealing with a sore left thumb.
